<p>The Shannon-Wiener species diversity index (
 <italic>SW</italic>) is expressed as:
 <disp-formula id="FD1-plants-08-00370">
  <label>(1)</label>
  <math id="mm1">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <mi>S</mi>
     <mi>W</mi>
     <mo>=</mo>
     <mo>−</mo>
     <mstyle displaystyle="true">
      <munderover>
       <mo>∑</mo>
       <mrow>
        <mi>i</mi>
        <mo>=</mo>
        <mn>1</mn>
       </mrow>
       <mi>S</mi>
      </munderover>
      <mrow>
       <msub>
        <mi>P</mi>
        <mi>i</mi>
       </msub>
       <msub>
        <mrow>
         <mi mathvariant="normal">lnP</mi>
        </mrow>
        <mi>i</mi>
       </msub>
      </mrow>
     </mstyle>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </disp-formula> where 
 <italic>S</italic> is the number of species, 
 <italic>Pi</italic> represents the diversity ratio of the 
 <italic>i</italic>th species, i.e., 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="mm2">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <msub>
      <mi>P</mi>
      <mi>i</mi>
     </msub>
     <mo>=</mo>
     <mfrac>
      <mrow>
       <msub>
        <mi>N</mi>
        <mi>i</mi>
       </msub>
      </mrow>
      <mi>N</mi>
     </mfrac>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>, where 
 <italic>N
  <sub>i</sub>
 </italic> is the total number of individuals of the 
 <italic>i</italic>th species, and 
 <italic>N</italic> is the total number of individuals of all species [
 <xref rid="B69-plants-08-00370" ref-type="bibr">69</xref>].
</p>
